      • matchPairs

        private boolean matchPairs(PairDistances respPDs,
                           PairDistances authPDs)
        For each pair in author's diagram, can we find one in response diagram with matching contents and distance?
        Parameters:
        respPDs - pairs of occupied cells in response and the distances between them
        authPDs - pairs of occupied cells in author's diagram and the distances between them
        Returns:
        true if all author pairs are found in response at matching distances

        Parameters:

        rowNums - list of lists of row numbers of the occupied cells of the diagram

      • compare

        private boolean compare(int respNum,
                        int authNum)
        Determines whether two orbital-orbital or state-state distances match according to the matching algorithm defined by energies.
        Parameters:
        respNum - the response orbital or state row number (FIXED_HEIGHT) or the distance between a pair of response orbitals or states
        authNum - the author's orbital or state row number (FIXED_HEIGHT) or the distance between a pair of author's orbitals or states
        Returns:
        true if the distances match

      • correlationsOK

        protected boolean correlationsOK()
        Determines whether the lines that connect the occupied cells in the two diagrams are the same. "Same" here means that the energy order of the occupied cells that are connected are the same within each column; e.g., the second-highest energy cell in column 2 is connected to the highest energy cell in column 3 in both diagrams.
        Returns:
        true if the lines connecting occupied cells are the same
